===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|punisceement|lang=fro}}, {{term|punisement|lang=fro}}, {{term|punishement|lang=fro}}, {{term|punissement|lang=fro}}, {{term|punisshement|lang=fro}} and the {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|punissement|lang=frm}}, from the {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|pugnissement|lang=fro}}, from {{term||puniss-|lang=fro}} (the long stem (see the {{etyl|fr|-}} {{term|-iss-|lang=fr}}) of {{term|punir|lang=fr||to punish}}) + {{term|-ment|lang=fr}} (see the {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|-ment|lang=en}}). Compare the {{etyl|en|-}} nouns {{term|punishing|lang=en}} and {{term|punition|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-punishment.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or process of [[punish]]ing, imposing and/or applying a [[sanction]].
# A [[penalty]] to punish wrongdoing, especially for [[crime]].
# A [[suffering]] by [[pain]] or [[loss]] imposed as [[retribution]]
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} Any [[treatment]] or experience so [[harsh]] it feels like being punished; rough handling
#: ''a vehicle that can take a lot of '''punishment'''''

